  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But the deal was that my father, being a doctor, he, he will obtain-- he will obtain rations for wood that will permit to heat the cottage.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And of course, my father was now in jail, so it became difficult, but my mother still used the old permit that also was terribly risky.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she got some wood, and we were staying there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "In the meantime, my mother was donating blood for few hundred rubles to buy-- to buy some food for my father and send it to jail to give him to in jail.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Afterwards when my father finally got out from the jail, he was saying that this food wasted even though my mother was donating blood and she was starving herself.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We have nothing to eat.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We. we. we waited in line for bread, 400 grams, and sometimes bread wouldn't arrive, so we wouldn't eat anything all day long.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But anyway she was giving the blood to buy him that food that went into jail that he never ate because there were 60 people in a room the size of maybe 20 by 20 feet lined up in layers-- four layers of bunks, four levels, and they would divide everything.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So when you divide a little bit of milk or frozen milk or whatever between 60 people or whatever, then nothing came, came to him.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Anyway, then another miracle happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "At that time, there was some agreement between Churchill and Stalin and they decided to organize a Polish army in Russia out of all these prisoners of war that Russians took in '39, I mean, these that were not shot in Katyn.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And there were many of them because they basically were shooting only the, the officers.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
